race.comment: EQUITABLE (1) resumed from a spell and was beaten 3.5 lengths over 900m at Scone. Began awkwardly in that and has a key jockey switch to Bullock. Will have come on from that and he finds a weak race. HE'STHECHIEF (2) resumed over 1000m at Scone and needed the outing. Two of his three previous starts have been at this track, and he's raced well in both. Will likely push forward and fitter is a threat. UNALIENABLE RIGHT (6) is likely the best of the debutants. Missed a long neck at Scone in his most recent trial and looks to have good ability. PARISSIDENT (8) raced well last preparation over this distance without cracking a win. Is running out of chances but she resumes again and should enjoy a soft run from an inside gate. She could get into the finish if presented on song.
